Document: StaticBody3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_staticbody3d.rst  
Summary: Class StaticBody3D reference section.  

Note: This class is part of the Godot Engine's 3D physics system, designed to represent non-dynamic objects that do not move under physics simulation. It inherits from RigidBody3D and is typically used for static elements in a scene that should not be affected by forces or collisions. Key Rule: StaticBody3D does not respond to physics forces but can still interact with other physics bodies through collision detection.
